article:
The 'Human Development Index' ('HDI') is a composite statistic of life
expectancy, education, and income indices to rank countries into four tiers of
human development. It was created by economist Mahbub ul Haq, followed by
economist Amartya Sen in 1990, and published by the United Nations
Development Programme. www.undp.org/content/undp/en/home.html
